Containerized Apache Kafka Streaming Platform on Docker
Objectives
Deploy a multi-service Apache Kafka cluster using Docker and Docker Compose, including Zookeeper coordination and a web-based management UI
Build and containerize Python producer, consumer, and stream-processing applications that communicate exclusively over a Docker bridge network
Validate end-to-end message flow and real-time stream processing using command-line Kafka tooling from within running containers
Prerequisites
Comfort navigating and editing files on a Linux/Ubuntu command line, including writing shell scripts and using a terminal text editor
Conceptual understanding of message brokers: what a topic, partition, producer, consumer, and consumer group are, and why offset tracking matters
Lab Environment
You will work on a dedicated AWS EC2 Ubuntu instance provided by Al Nafi. The instance has a base Ubuntu installation; you will install all required tools in Task 1.

