Design and execute an installation sequence that results in a working Docker Engine (version 24 or later) and the Docker Compose plugin available as docker compose (with a space, not a hyphen) on your Ubuntu instance. Your sequence must add Docker's official APT repository, install the engine and compose plugin from that repository, configure the current user to run Docker without sudo, and confirm the daemon is active.

